Ceratopetalum apetalum

   [4427.jpg]
    Authority   D. D.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Rosales:Cunoniaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4427

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A medium sized tree usually reaching 25 m in height,
   while the trunk may reach 90 cm in diameter. The stems are pale
   coloured and cylindrical with short, small buttresses on larger trees.
   The crown is normally quit small. Heartwood pinkish-brown, fine
   textured and straight grained. USES The wood seasons well and it is
   easy to work and glu. It is used for plywood, veneers, joinery,
   furniture, lining, turnery, carving and rifle butts. GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial. COMMON NAMES Coachwood, Scented satinwood. FURTHER INF In
   Australia, the latitudinal range of the tree is 28-35.5Â°S and it occur
   in the coastal rainforests at elevations between 100-900 m.

   Sources
   SOURCES (C. apetalum D. Don)
   Boland D 1984 pp 114-117 [TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, TEXT, FER, PH, USE]

